I also understand that visitors from overseas, (Europe in particular),
should apply for medical coverage in their home nation, before they travel.
The EU and/or many National Governments have reciprocal arrangements to
cover emergency medical treatment in the USA. Before I relocated to the USA
for good, in 2000, I always applied for the relevant coverage forms, and/or
took out personal medical insurance cover as a back up. This worked well for
me, although I personally never had to use it.

Dorian J Blagg

