Sometimes, medical emergencies can also occur from seemingly innocuous
conditions. A few years ago, we held a convention in a northern city
known for its 2-week &quot;mosquito season.&quot; One of our new staff members
was a very recent transplant from the UK. We went to an outdoor event
one evening and were all battling the mosquitos---but the new staff
member had never been exposed to mosquitos before (!). She developed
an allergic reaction and had to be taken to the hospital. She was kept
overight and was fine the next day, but one never knows...

